cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it presents an end-to-end approach for tracking objects using raw laser input data. The use of a recurrent neural network (RNN) also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the focus on tracking objects in a crowded urban environment suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques such as spatial transformer modules suggests that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
